Update changelog

I also inserted a few things in the "Unreleased" section. Just as a
teaser.

Remove less dir reference from package.json

We'll include the less file in the package, but it lives in css/ now.

Clean refs to old less/ directory

less/ no longer exists. Change refs to css/ instead.

Move timepicker.less into css dir

We'll publish a package with js/ and css/ dirs containing the build
artifacts. We no longer need a less/ directory.

Ignore node_modules and _layouts

Correct a typo, and ignore node_modules just for S's and G's.

Ignore junk in bower.json, provide more metadata

Modeled off of jquery's bower.json file. Nothing fancy.

Pull request #294 fixed incompatibilities with bootstrap and jquery
libs, but the jquery team moved the location of their build artifacts in
the bower package.

Timepicker will now close its widget when tab out

If the timepicker widget is showing when the user
tabs out of the input control (either via
SHIFT+TAB or just TAB), the widget was still
showing on the screen.  This commit fixes it so
that the widget will close if it is open at the
time the user tabs out.

New option: showWidgetOnAddonClick

New option: showWidgetOnAddonClick

Default value is true (for backward compatibility).

In current version, if the input has a add-on time icon, the widget does not show up when the input gets focus, as in bootstrap-datepicker. To make things a bit more consistent, I added this new option.
